          <div data-content-element-selector="p, .js-buylink-item-container" data-allowed-classes-selector="js-buylink-item-container">
                <p>After working in game development for over four decades, Peter Molyneux is calling it quits after he finishes his god game Masters of Albion--that is, if you take his word for it.</p><p>Speaking to Edge (via <a href="https://www.pcgamer.com/games/sim/emperor-of-overpromising-peter-molyneux-says-hes-done-with-games-after-masters-of-albion-which-is-also-his-redemption-title/" data-target="true" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">PC Gamer</a>), Molyneux called Masters of Albion his "redemption title," adding: "... it's my last game. It just is." The game was <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/peter-molyneux-debuts-new-god-game-masters-of-albion/1100-6525994/" data-ref-id="1100-6525994">announced back in August 2024</a> at Gamescom Opening Night Live; at the time of its announcement, Molyneux had already secretly been working on the title for three years.</p>



    
